Understanding interaction effects in (logistic) regression models

facebook <- readr::read_rds("data/facebook.rds")
register("facebook")

Facebook ads

result <- logistic(
  facebook,
  rvar = "click",
  evar = c("age", "gender", "ad"),
  lev = "yes"
)
summary(result)

Trying to uncover interactions using a Neural Network.

result <- nn(
  facebook,
  rvar = "click",
  evar = c("age", "gender", "ad"),
  lev = "yes",
  size = 1,
  seed = 1234
)
summary(result)

Update the logistic regression based on insights generated using the Neural Network:

result <- logistic(
  facebook,
  rvar = "click",
  evar = c("age", "gender", "ad"),
  lev = "yes",
  int = "gender:ad"
)
summary(result)

Changing the order of the ad levels

## change factor levels
facebook <- mutate(facebook, gender = refactor(gender, levs = c("female","male"), repl = ""))
result <- logistic(
  facebook,
  rvar = "click",
  evar = c("age", "gender", "ad"),
  lev = "yes",
  int = "gender:ad"
)
